{
  "stem": "9730.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And from there, we, you know, went on-- on these-- went on the invasion fleet.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I mean, we-- we came after the invasion had already begun.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I-- I-- I landed on-- it was called Utah Sugar Red, which-- Utah Beach.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The nearest town that is well known was Sainte-Mere-Eglise, and where we dug in-- actually took over some of the foxholes left by the previous division that we relieved.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we were sort of-- we had to stay there until the breakthrough at Saint-Lo, which was-- I believe was early in July, after which we were on the move, you know.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And so we went through the Normandy campaign and then went somewhat south to a city called Angers.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And from there we went to the city of Lance in-- more-- more in the east of France.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And from there to-- well, we saw, of course, the liberation of Paris, although I myself was not in Paris but some 20 miles outside of Paris at that time.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I was actively engaged, but I-- that-- that depends exactly how you mean that.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My job was to interrogate prisoners of war.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I-- I-- I-- I was not at that time doing any shooting myself, but-- but-- but we were of course exposed to all the same mortar fire, artillery fire, and-- and anything else that anybody else was.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh yeah.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we, you know-- we found that some of those prisoners, in the earlier days especially, were still somewhat arrogant.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But we-- we usually were able to-- to get some information out of them.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And also, by interrogating many of them, and we could play some of them up against the others-- you know, that so-and-so said such and such about your unit.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "How about that?",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
